Commentary.Commentary: We are back. The players are out in the middle. Zak Crawley and Ben Duckett to open for England. A small period for them to tackle. Here is Abrar Ahmed to bowl first.
...SECOND INNINGS...

So, 304 could be challenging if Pakistan bowl well. We have seen the ball turn and turn quite a lot. England however, have tackled spin brilliantly so far. Can they tackle this nervy period which is going to come up now? We will find out.

Pakistan will be disappointed with that effort. After electing to bat, they would have been aiming for something over 400 and there were times in this innings where they did find themselves in a strong position but kept losing wickets at crucial times. The Azam run out was crucial, had he stayed longer, maybe above 350 would have been scored.

The key for the visitors was they always managed to pick wickets when the game was drifting away. The two spinners were excellent. Jack Leach and Rehan Ahmed were arguably the picks. The pacers also did a handy job, they managed to keep the pressure on. Stokes will be a happy man after being asked to field.

Pakistan have managed to cross the 300-run mark. Really not sure though if this is a good total or not but we feel it is a competitive one. However, it will be England who will be the happier of the two sides at the moment.

Commentary.Howout: b Jack Leach

OUT! AZAM IS RUN OUT! Big, big moment in the game. Flatter and on middle, nudged to the right of square leg. Salman calls for a quick single and Azam is hesitant at first but then runs across. The fielder picks up and throws it to Foakes, the keeper who had to collect on the other side of the stumps. He runs, picks one-handedly and whips the bails off. Babar looked short and the replay confirms but it also shows that Foakes' other hand nudged the bails first, eventually though one bail came off but he managed to remove the other bail quickly with the ball in hand. Harry Brook with some excellent fielding, Ben Foakes with a wonderful piece of keeping.
Commentary.Howout: run out (Harry Brook / Ben Foakes)

...Day 1, Session 3...

A session that England will be happy with. They have taken two wickets in this session on a flat pitch. This session was more for spinners. Rehan Ahmed came back nicely as he bowled much better than in the opening session and got his debut wicket as well. Mohammad Rizwan was hoping for a big stay but gave away his wicket. England stayed in the game and got their rewards while for Pakistan, it is Babar Azam who is keeping the score ticking. He is batting very well but needs Salman to give him a helping hand. On another dull pitch, England will be happy with how things panned out. They will hope for another big session. Join us back in a while for the final session.

OUT! THAT IS A CLEAN CATCH! That is a superb take from Pope! Rehan Ahmed gets his first Test wicket! A proud, proud moment for him and it is an important wicket as this stand was going along really well. Excellent bowling too. He bowled the googly on the last ball which beat the bat, this time it is the leg spinner, it lands outside off and turns back in nicely. Shakeel looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge, hits the pad and then lobs on the pitch. Pope towards the end, dives forward and takes it with one hand inches above the ground. England appeal but the umpire asks them to wait. He walks to his partner and then takes it upstairs after a chat. Soft signal is OUT! Replays show that is a clean catch. England yet again manage to pick a wicket just as the game was drifting away.
Commentary.Howout: c Ollie Pope b Rehan Ahmed

... DAY 1, SESSION 2 ...

Pakistan will hope they can get another good stand after the break! Azam is well set and the hosts will hope he can go on. England on the other hand, will want to continue to chip away at the wickets. An important session awaits in a bit.

That wicket right at the end will make England feel really good about this session! However, we believe, it is a shared one as Pakistan have managed to score at a decent rate. The start though was not the best for them as they lost two before 50. Ali and Azam though steadied the ship with a 50-plus stand. The two looked at ease out there and it seemed like this session would finish in the favor of Pakistan but at the stroke of the break, Ollie Robinson struck a crucial blow to get England back into the game.

Has that been taken? Foakes is sure but the soft signal is NOT OUT! ULTRA EDGE SHOWS A SPIKE! By the initial replays, it seems like it has carried. OUT! That is indeed a clean catch and England have a wicket at the stroke of Lunch. The short ball works again. This is on the body, Ali looks to pull, it goes off the glove and towards Foakes who dives forward and takes it. There is an appeal. The umpire is not sure if it carried or not and has a word with his partner. Replays show that it has. Yet another Pakistan batter walks back after getting off to a start. THAT WILL BE LUNCH!
Commentary.Howout: c Ben Foakes b Ollie Robinson

PAKISTAN (PLAYING XI) - Abdullah Shafique, Shan Masood (IN FOR Imam-ul-Haq), Azhar Ali (IN FOR Mohammad Nawaz), Babar Azam (C), Mohammad Rizwan (WK), Agha Salman, Saud Shakeel, Faheem Ashraf, Nauman Ali (IN FOR Zahid Mahmood), Mohammad Wasim (IN FOR Mohammad Ali), Abrar Ahmed.

ENGLAND (PLAYING XI) - Zak Crawley, Ben Duckett, Ollie Pope, Joe Root, Harry Brook, Ben Stokes (C), Ben Foakes (WK) (IN FOR Will Jacks), Rehan Ahmed (IN FOR James Anderson), Ollie Robinson, Mark Wood, Jack Leach.
TOSS - Pakistan have won the toss and ELECTED TO BAT!

It is time for the third and the final Test of this series between Pakistan and England. The visitors have already bagged the series with a game to go but will be eyeing a whitewash. Pakistan on the other hand, will be desperate for a win. They have failed to win any of their mast five Tests at home and will be eager to end on a high. They have been outplayed by England so far, can they somehow manage to put up their best game and make it 2-1? We will find out. Toss and teams in a bit.
... MATCH DAY ...

Host Pakistan will be looking to salvage some pride when they face England in the third and final game of the test series. England lead by 2-0 and would be looking to whitewash the series. The first test was a historic one and many records were broken in that game. The England batters ran a havoc on the first day and scored over 500 runs and a few of the batters scored a ton. Pakistan did reply well but the visitors won the game comfortably. The second Test was a tight one and there were pretty low scores on the board. England was bundled for just 281 runs in the 1st innings but they came up with a solid reply and bowled out Pakistan for just 202 runs. They set up a total target of 354 runs and won by the finest margin of just 26 runs. Babar Azam will be hoping for a win in this game and walk out with some pride in this dead rubber. On the other hand, Ben Stokes will be hoping that the side can guard against complacency and play to their potential in the final Test. Let's hope for a competitive game.

Now pakistan's first aim will be to knock this off with losing a wicket and then bat long, still lot of time in the game and Pakistan would want to give England a big total. England on the other hand, will hope to take a wicket or two before Stumps.

Pakistan will be disappointing at conceding the lead! Their spinners bowled really well to begin with to dismiss the top five quickly but once the ball got really soft, it was hard work for them, they though even failed to contain the runs when Brook and Foakes were batting. However, they will still be happy with not letting the visitors run away with the game. Nauman Ali was the pick , Abrar Ahmed was good and Mohammad Wasim impressed on his debut.

A really good batting effort from England and they have Harry Brook and Ben Foakes to thank! A few of their top order batters got off to starts but did not make it could. They were struggling at one time when Stokes was run. They were trailing by over 150 but these two put on a brilliant 100-plus run stand. Brook scored a ton and Foakes scored a fine fifty. Brook fell but Foakes continued. Along with the tail and with a lot of help from Wood, he took his side past Pakistan's total. England will be very happy with where they are placed in the game despite it being just a slender lead.

For Pakistan, it has been hard work, the pitch seems to have lost its zip, there is a turn but slow turn. The spinners do not look threatening. Pakistan though will be hoping this break works in their favor and they get a wicket after it. They would be hoping for some sort of a lead! Do they have a hero in them? Stay tuned for the final and what could be a very important session.

OUT! IT IS STOKES WHO HAS TO WALK BACK! Massive confusion and this is the only way this pair could have been broken! The two were looking at so much ease and this is a disastrous start for the visitors after the break. Have to say, it was Brook who was at fault here. This is a full ball, he clips it through mid-wicket. Ali does really well. He makes a lot of ground to his left, dives and pushes it back in. The batters have ran two till then. They do go upstairs to check if the stop is clean first which is fine and then who is the one who is run out and replays show it is Stokes! He shows the thumps up to Brook as he walks back which is a good gesture but pretty sure he will be fuming from within. Both Stokes and Azam have been run out in this game so far. Pakistan's 304 nnow looks far away.

We are back for what could well be a very important session! Harry Brook and Ben Stokes make their way out to the middle. They are followed by the Pakistan players. Abrar Ahmed to begin. Here we go...
... DAY 2, SESSION 2 ...

Pakistan went for the spin as there was not much for the pacers. At the start, they were not disciplined but the Pakistani bowlers grew as the game progressed. Both, Abrar and Ali bowled in tandem and the latter got two wickets in two balls. Pakistan will be happy with how things have gone till now. The spinners have to toil more as they will be the ones looked upto for wickets. England trail by 164 runs at the break. A fascinating opening session has ended. We feel England will come with more intent after the break. Join us back after the break for the second session.

So, 133 runs were scored in this session but England have lost three wickets as well. They will be happy they are going in the break with a back of a good stand building between the skipper and Brook. Both have certainly been a bit more aggressive than we saw from the other batters. England started Day 2 with Pope and Ben Duckett. Both looked composed but the latter fell later on. Pope too fell after getting his fifty. Brook was then joined by his skipper who is scoring runs freely and will look to continue further.

Welcome to the action of Day 2. The wicket of Crawley in the final few minutes of Day 1 has just given Pakistan an extra edge. Still a long way to go but with the pitch not helping the seamers much. The spinners will look to generate turn and look for wickets. It will be interesting to see how the Englishmen bat. Their aggressive way or will put on a clinical display. We saw 11 wickets fall on Day 1, will the pitch offer the same course on Day 2? Stay tuned for more updates.
...Day 2, Session 1...
So, Day 1 has gone by and both teams are still equallly in the game. Join us back on Day 2 at 1030 IST (0500 GMT) and early for the build up. Cheers!

So, an eventful final period of Day 1 and have to say, that wicket of Zak Crawley has just pushed Pakistan on top in this match. Pakistan will be happy after how things went out. After electing to bat first, they didn't have a good start but the knock from Azhar Ali and Saud Shakeel turned out to be handy. It was the stand between Azam and Salman that flourished. Pakistan were in a really good position at that time but lost Azam through a run out. Salman too after his fifty fell and Pakistan bundled out just over 300. England had to play a tricky period and in that process lost Zak Crawley, which they will be very disappointed.

He gets pinned on the back pad, plumb, an appeal follows for LBW and up goes the finger. Just what Pakistan needed.

For England, it was the spinners who did the trick yet again. First it was Leach who got rid of the top three and then it was Rehan Ahmed who weaved his magic. He bagged a fifer on debut and has given his side a real chance to win this. England will back themselves to knock it off but the question is, can the Pakistan bowling finally arrive? We will find out.

Pakistan will be very disappointed, just the two batters showed some fight and they were Azam and Saud Shakeel, the rest just surrendered. They lost three in no time after taing the lead. Then there was a big partnership between Azam and Saud. However, once Azam fell, there was a procession. From 164 for 3 they have been bundled out for 216.

It is Rehan Ahmed who is leading his side off the field and rightly so! What a performance from the youngster. He has been exceptional and is the main reason why his side is in total control of this game now. England need just the 167 to complete the whitewash and they will be pretty confident to do so.

More of the same is what England will want after the break! Pakistan's lead is below 150 and England will hope they can keep it to under 200. Pakistan are in desperate need of a partnership, can Agha Salman and Faheem Ashraf provide it? We will find out.

Yet another session with three wickets in it for England and they are in control of the game now! The start though was all Pakistan, Babar Azam and Saud Shakeel looked at ease and were milking the bowlers. The two got to their half tons and the tide then was towards Pakistan. However, it was Rehan Ahmed who turned things around, his introdution got three wickets in no time for the visitors and it was the three big ones, Babar Azam, Mohammad Rizwan and Saud Shakeel to turn the look of the game completely.

We are back for the afternoon session! Pakistan's lead is one short of fifty, the two batters Babar Azam and Saud Shakeel will look to build on that. They walk out to resume their innings. Jack Leach to begin. Here we go...
... DAY 3, SESSION 2 ...

England will not be that disappointed as well. They were under pressure but Jack Leach took three wickets in no time and put Pakistan on the back foot. Although, the ball has got too soft and isn't much doing. Rehan Ahmed was not used but we feel, he and Leach will have to bowl in tandem to scrap some turns and break this stand. A long second session coming up. Nothing to separate for now. Join us back at 1310 IST (0740 GMT) for the action.

So, the repair work has started for Pakistan after losing three wickets in no time. Both, Azam and Shakeel will be happy as they have done well to mold a good stand. Pakistan were off to a really good start and both openers played with intent and scored 50 in no time but lost wickets in quick succession. However, these two have done well to ease out the pressure and build a partnership. Pakistan have a lead close to 50 but they need to go strong and bat another session without losing any wickets.

Welcome everyone to the action of Day 3. Till now in the last two matches, the tides were favouring one team at this point but it’s not the case in this match despite England clinching the series. It is very hard to say who will win from here on as both teams have given their best till now. Pakistan though trail by 29 runs so they will first look to cut the deficit before putting in a strong lead. England on the other hand will hope for wickets. Stay tuned…
...Day 3,Session 1...

The game now is nicely set-up for the coming days. Pakistan did have a chance to actually take nice control of the game but a fightback from Brook and Foakes has seen the game evenly poised. Pakistan will hope they can knock this deficit off without losing a wicket whereas England will hope to take a wicket or two at the start of Day 3. An important day follows. Do join us for the action which begins at 1030 IST (0500 GMT). The build-up begins a lot earlier. Till then, goodbye and take care!

Pakistan have got through the nery period unscathed and they have got down the deficit to just the 29 runs! England, bowled tight lines and lengths but there was not a lot on offer, yes, a couple of balls did turn but it was slow turn and something that the batters easily negotiated.

That is it from this game! The trophy is presentated to Stokes, he now walks towards his team to celebrate. A top show from England, not easy to come here in Pakistan and beat them and England have whitewashed the hosts. Brilliant! That is it from this game and this series. We hope you enjoyed our company. Until next time, take care and goodbye!

Ben Stokes says it has been the perfect tour for them. States they want to play in a certain way and they did but he is happy with how they adapted and everybody stood up when needed. Mentions he has a lot of belief in his teammates and that is what helps them to get the wins and all the players are quite confident. Ends by saying it was a team effort but Brook has been brilliant and Rehan Ahmed was excellent in this game and he is really happy for him.

Babar Azam says he is very disappointed, they were just not good enough but credits to the England side for the way they played. Adds they did not bat that well in the first innings, they were decent in patches but not good overall. Mentions it is difficult when your best pacer is not fit but he is happy with how his bowlers have bowled. Mentions there were a lot of positives but they need to improve.

Harry Brook, Man of the Match and Series, says it has been his best tour, nobody has won 3-0 and it is a top effort. States he was very annoyed when he got out to Abrar and he was happy to learn from his mistake.
... PRESENTATION TIME ...

Pakistan's problem in their second innings was they lost wickets in heaps, they began well with the bat but Leach then ran through the top order. Azam and Saud then put up a 100-run stand to change the tide in their favor again but it was then the Rehan Ahmed show, the youngster spun a web and bagged a fifer on debut. His spell absolutely killed the game as Pakistan only managed to give England a target of 167 which the visitors easily knocked off.

Right from Day 1 though England have shown great character in this game! They were asked to bowl on a flat wicket but they managed to bowl Pakistan out for an average score. Jack Leach was the star for England with a four-fer. FOr Pakistan, a few of their batters got off to starts but none went onto make it big and that is what they needed. However, despite not getting a big score, the Pakistan spinners came to the fore and had England five down for below 150. Harry Brook though along with Ben Foakes led the fight back, the two added over 100 and helped England take a slender lead.

Coming to the game now, this was never in doubt when Day 4 started, Pakistan needed something magical if they were to pull off a victory but the overnight batters, Ben Duckett and Ben Stokes ensured there are no wickets to fall and scored the remaining runs in no time.

WHITEWASH COMPLETE! England have yet again outplayed Pakistan, another stunning victory for a side which just seems unbeatable at the moment. A huge round of applause for Azhar Ali as he makes his way back to the pavillion, not the finish he would have wanted but he surely had a career to remember.

Time for the action to begin. Ben Stokes and Ben Duckett walk out to the centre and it is Abrar Ahmed to begin with the ball.

Pakistan need nothing short of a miracle to avoid a whitewash. They'll need someone to give a once in a lifetime performance with the ball. 8 wickets is what they need and England need just the 55 runs. The visitors will be wanting to score this as quickly as possible. How long will it take them? We will find out.
... DAY 4, SESSION 1 ...

When Babar Azam and Saud Shakeel were batting, it looked like Pakistan will not give away this game easily but then came the debutant who bowled after almost 40 overs and went onto claim wickets of Azam, Saud Shakeel, Rizwan and Salman. That just kept Pakistan hanging on a single thread and eventually were bowled out. It was Jack Leach who handled the top order and then the youngster, Ahmed. Now then, Pakistan need to pull a rabbit out of the hat. Join us back for Day 4 at 1030 IST (0500 GMT) and earlier for the build up for all the action. Till then, cheers!

The 'Bazball' is in full flow and England are just an hour's play away from the whitewash. What an innings this was from England. Chasing around 160, they have left minimal work for Day 4 as both, Zak Crawley and Ben Duckett came out all guns blazing taking the spinners to the cleaners. The pacers calmed things down but the runs kept on coming somehow. Zak Crawley fell but Duckett along with his skipper will sleep cozily knowing the results are inevitable.
